milestones.description: Paul Stirling has become the top scorer for IRE in ODIs with 4006 runs, going past Porterfield's 3968
Kevin O'Brien has broken the record for most catches (63) in ODIs for IRE, going past Porterfield's 62

stories.title: Tim Murtagh's maiden five-for wraps up series win for Ireland
stories.subTitle: Ireland v Zimbabwe, 2nd ODI, Belfast
stories.seoTitle: Tim Murtagh's maiden five-for wraps up series win for Ireland
stories.summary: Fifties from Williams and Burl kept Zimbabwe in the hunt in a chase of 243, but Murtagh picked up wickets at key moments to bowl his side to a narrow victory
